The '2008â09 A-League' was the fourth season of the Australasian A-League
association football competition. Two new clubs, North Queensland Thunder and
Gold Coast Galaxy had received
tentative licences from the FFA but these were revoked for the 2008–09
season on 12 March 2008. Expansion plans are on hold until the
2009–10 season. Based on their 2007–08 performances, the and the
competed in the 2009 AFC Champions League for the first time.

Changes to the league included:
* The introduction of both a youth league and women's league aligned with A-
  League clubs.
* An increase in the salary cap to A$1.9 million.
* The addition of a Junior Marquee player. (A player under the age of 23 who has
  up to A$150,000 of his salary outside of the cap.
* Injury replacement players can only match the injured players' salary, or have
  any excess included within the total Salary Cap.
* A-League squads will be increased to 30 or 35. (inclusive of Youth
  Team Players)
